properties.Summary:

Conditions will gradually improve this evening over the communities of Umiujaq, Inukjuak, Puvirnituq and Salluit. properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Significant snowfall is expected. Locations: northern Labrador. Total snowfall: 20 to 40 cm. Time span: Wednesday morning until Thursday afternoon. Remarks: The snow will be heaviest on Wednesday, with lighter accumulations on Thursday. The snow may also mix with rain along parts of the coast on Thursday. There is some uncertainty as to where the highest accumulations will occur, but some areas will likely receive substantial amounts of snowfall. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NLstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NLwx.

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Frost may damage some crops in frost-prone areas. Temperatures will drop near the freezing mark overnight tonight. In addition, the unseasonably relatively cool weather will continue for several more days. Accordingly, frost advisory over Southwestern Quebec could be continued over the following nights and mornings through Wednesday morning or even Thursday in some areas. ### Frost advisories are issued when temperatures are expected to reach the freezing mark during the growing season, leading to potential damage and destruction to plants and crops. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to QCstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #QCStorm.

properties.Title: Frost Advisory In Effect
properties.Summary:

May 11 marks the beginning of the 2020 Frost Advisory season for these regions in Ontario. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
